Initial runbook for story [Create Storage Account (with SFTP) and deploy it using ADO pipeline](https://tools.hmcts.net/jira/browse/DTSPO-27441).
Will be expanded by later stories in Epic [ServiceNow MySQL Flexible Server creation](https://tools.hmcts.net/jira/browse/DTSPO-27439).

## 1. Overview

Provision an SFTP-enabled Azure Storage Account as a secure landing zone for ServiceNow data dump files prior 
to MySQL restore. Deployed via Azure DevOps pipeline into subscription DTS-SHAREDSERVICES-PROD 
with private network access from `ss-prod-vnet` only.

## 2. Current Scope (THIS STORY ONLY)

In scope now:

- Resource Group creation
- SFTP-enabled Storage Account (standard general-purpose v2)
- Private Endpoint on `ss-prod-vnet`
- Azure DevOps pipeline automating above

Out of scope (future stories): MySQL Flexible Server, restore procedure, auto-shutdown, AAD DB auth.

